						<summary>

						

						<p>On a slab set up near the Jakkēru-bhāvi.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 971, Virōdhi, Phālguṇa śu. 13</hi>, corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1050 A.D., February 7.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records gifts of lands totalling 129 <hi rend="italic">mattar</hi> and 450 <hi rend="italic">kamma</hi> to god Sōmēśvaradēva by Jasakabbe. It refers to a Karttikēyadēva-tapōvana.</p>						

						</summary>
